This defiantly falls under Haskell not being noob friendly.<p>If you are in the REPL, you want to do `let sumOfElements [] = 0`<p>If you want multiline input, you open with `:{` and close with `:}`. Both of these need to be on their own line. For example:<p><pre><code>    Prelude>:{
    Prelude| let sum [] = 0
    Prelude|     sum (x:xs) = x + sum xs
    Prelude|:}
</code></pre>
As tdinkar points out, it is often easier to define your functions if a file and load that file from the REPL.
